SIMPLE: bushwhacker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bushwhacker
<hw>Bush"whack`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One accustomed to beat about, or travel through, bushes.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were gallant <qex>bushwhackers</qex>, and hunters of raccoons
by moonlight.</q> <rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A guerrilla; a marauding assassin; one who pretends
to be a peaceful citizen, but secretly harasses a hostile force or its
sympathizers.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark> <rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushwhacking</ent>⟦br⟧
